'''Arthur "Art" St. Clair Chapman''' (October 28, 1912<ref>other sources report his year of birth: ''1913''</ref> &ndash; February 3, 1986) was a [[Canada|Canadian]] [[basketball]] player who competed in the [[1936 Summer Olympics]].

Born in [[Victoria, British Columbia|Victoria]], Chapman was part of the Canadian basketball team, which won the silver medal. He played all six matches including the final. He was the younger brother of [[Chuck Chapman]], who also participated at the Berlin Games. He died in [[Nanaimo, British Columbia]].

